{"parse":{"title":"James C. Burt","pageid":18580714,"revid":850173756,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div role=\"note\" class=\"hatnote navigation-not-searchable\">For other people named James Burt, see <a href=\"/wiki/James_Burt_(disambiguation)\" class=\"mw-redirect mw-disambig\" title=\"James Burt (disambiguation)\">James Burt (disambiguation)</a>.</div>\n<p><b>James Caird Burt</b> (August 29, 1921<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup> \u2013 2012) was an American <a href=\"/wiki/Gynecologist\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Gynecologist\">gynecologist</a> who was sometimes nicknamed the \"Love Surgeon.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-ap1988_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ap1988-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> After practicing for two decades while based in <a href=\"/wiki/Dayton,_Ohio\" title=\"Dayton, Ohio\">Dayton, Ohio</a>, Burt was sued by female patients for altering their <a href=\"/wiki/Vulva\" title=\"Vulva\">vulvas</a> without their <a href=\"/wiki/Informed_consent\" title=\"Informed consent\">informed consent</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-horny_3-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-horny-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Career\">Career</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=James_C._Burt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Career\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Burt was born in <a href=\"/wiki/Dayton,_Ohio\" title=\"Dayton, Ohio\">Dayton, Ohio</a> and earned his <a href=\"/wiki/Doctor_of_Medicine\" title=\"Doctor of Medicine\">M.D.</a> from the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Rochester_School_of_Medicine\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"University of Rochester School of Medicine\">University of Rochester School of Medicine</a> in 1945. He was licensed in Ohio in 1951.\n</p><p>Burt began performing \"love surgery\" in 1966.<sup id=\"cite_ref-horny_3-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-horny-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> In his 1975 book, <i>Surgery of Love,</i> Burt wrote: \"Women are structurally inadequate for <a href=\"/wiki/Sexual_intercourse\" title=\"Sexual intercourse\">intercourse</a>. This is a pathological condition amenable by surgery.\" He claimed his surgery would turn women into \"horny little mice\" and asserted that \"the difference between rape and rapture is salesmanship.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-horny_3-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-horny-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-burt1975_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-burt1975-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> Burt's procedures caused <a href=\"/wiki/Sexual_dysfunction\" title=\"Sexual dysfunction\">sexual dysfunction</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Infection\" title=\"Infection\">infection</a> and the need for <a href=\"/wiki/Corrective_surgery\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Corrective surgery\">corrective surgery</a> in many patients.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ap1989_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-ap1989-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 1988, women subjected to the procedure came forward, eventually initiating several lawsuits.<sup id=\"cite_ref-pd1988_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-pd1988-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>  He voluntarily surrendered his license in January 1989, thereby avoiding a medical board hearing which might have uncovered more evidence against him. He subsequently divorced and declared bankruptcy due to the victim lawsuits totaling <a href=\"/wiki/United_States_dollar\" title=\"United States dollar\">USD</a>$21 million.<sup id=\"cite_ref-brower1989_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-brower1989-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Burt died in Dayton, OH in 2012.<sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=James_C._Burt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Burt, James C. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://familysearch.org/\">\"United States Public Records Index\"</a>. familysearch<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">6 November</span> 2013</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=United+States+Public+Records+Index&amp;rft.pub=familysearch&amp;rft.aulast=Burt&amp;rft.aufirst=James+C&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Ffamilysearch.org%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJames+C.+Burt\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-ap1988-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-ap1988_2-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Associate Press (December 9, 1988). Ohio \"love surgeon\" called up on ethics charges. <i><a href=\"/wiki/Bangor_Daily_News\" title=\"Bangor Daily News\">Bangor Daily News</a></i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-horny-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-horny_3-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-horny_3-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-horny_3-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a href=\"/wiki/Isabel_Wilkerson\" title=\"Isabel Wilkerson\">Isabel Wilkerson</a> (December 11, 1988). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?sec=health&amp;res=940DE5D81630F932A25751C1A96E948260\">\"Charges Against Doctor Bring Ire and Questions\"</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Times\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New York Times\">New York Times</a></i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2010-10-26</span></span>. <q>Dr. Burt, once a well-regarded physician considered merely eccentric, began the special surgery in 1966. Explaining his philosophy in his 1975 book, <i>Surgery of Love,</i> Dr. Burt wrote: <i>Women are structurally inadequate for intercourse. This is a pathological condition amenable to surgery.</i> In franker terms, he also said that his surgery would turn women into <i>horny little mice</i> and asserted that <i>the difference between rape and rapture is salesmanship.</i></q></cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=New+York+Times&amp;rft.atitle=Charges+Against+Doctor+Bring+Ire+and+Questions&amp;rft.date=1988-12-11&amp;rft.au=Isabel+Wilkerson&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fquery.nytimes.com%2Fgst%2Ffullpage.html%3Fsec%3Dhealth%26res%3D940DE5D81630F932A25751C1A96E948260&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AJames+C.+Burt\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-burt1975-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-burt1975_4-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Burt, James C. and Joan Burt (1975). <i>Surgery of Love.</i> Carlton Press <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-8062-0158-4\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-8062-0158-4\">0-8062-0158-4</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-ap1989-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-ap1989_5-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Associated Press (January 20, 1989). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=950DE5D71F3EF933A15752C0A96F948260\">Ohio Doctor Offers to Quit</a>. <i><a href=\"/wiki/New_York_Times\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New York Times\">New York Times</a></i></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-pd1988-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-pd1988_6-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Women go public with charges against Dayton surgeon, Dr James C Burt. <i><a href=\"/wiki/The_Plain_Dealer\" title=\"The Plain Dealer\">The Plain Dealer</a></i> 29 Oct, 1988, pg. 01 sec. A</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-brower1989-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-brower1989_7-0\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Brower, Montgomery; Breu, Giovanna (March 27, 1989). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20119884,00.html\">James Burt's 'Love Surgery' Was Supported to Boost Pleasure, but Some Patients Say It Brought Pain.</a> <i><a href=\"/wiki/People_(magazine)\" title=\"People (magazine)\">People</a></i> (retrieved April 15, 2011)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.patient-safety.com/burt.htm\">Dr. James Burt - The Love Surgeon</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=James_C._Burt&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.patient-safety.com/burt.htm\">Dr. James Burt: The Love Surgeon</a> via patient-safety.com</li></ul>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><span style=\"vertical-align: middle; background:transparent\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Flag_of_the_United_States.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Flag of United States\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a4/Flag_of_the_United_States.svg/30px-Flag_of_the_United_States.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"16\" class=\"thumbborder\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a4/Flag_of_the_United_States.svg/45px-Flag_of_the_United_States.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/a/a4/Flag_of_the_United_States.svg/60px-Flag_of_the_United_States.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"1235\" data-file-height=\"650\" /></a><span style=\"margin-left:-30px; margin-right:0px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Scientist.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Scientist icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/Scientist.svg/30px-Scientist.svg.png\" width=\"30\" height=\"30\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/Scientist.svg/45px-Scientist.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/03/Scientist.svg/60px-Scientist.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"400\" data-file-height=\"400\" /></a></span></span> <a href=\"/wiki/File:Rod_of_Asclepius2.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Rod of Asclepius2.svg\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Rod_of_Asclepius2.svg/10px-Rod_of_Asclepius2.svg.png\" width=\"10\" height=\"32\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Rod_of_Asclepius2.svg/15px-Rod_of_Asclepius2.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e3/Rod_of_Asclepius2.svg/20px-Rod_of_Asclepius2.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"251\" data-file-height=\"804\" /></a></td><td><i>This biographical article related to medicine in the United States is a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Stub\" title=\"Wikipedia:Stub\">stub</a>. You can help W